==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Officiate
<hw>Of*fi"ci*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Officiated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Officiating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[LL.
<ets>officiare</ets>. See <er>Office</er>.]</ety> <def>To act as an
officer in performing a duty; to transact the business of an office or
public trust; to conduct a public ceremony or service.</def> <rj><au>Bp.
Stillingfleet.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Officiate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Officiate
<hw>Of*fi"ci*ate</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To discharge, perform, or
supply, as an official duty or function.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Merely to <qex>officiate</qex> light⟦br⟧
Round this opacous earth.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Officiator</ent>⟦br⟧
